Three IOS components:
  Kernel services
  Kernel support services
  Network support services


Kernel Services
  Scheduler
    non-preemptive
    event-driven
    process is like thread in other OS's terminology
    4 process priorities: low, medium, high, critical
    process has its own stack, stack size specified at creation

Memory Management
  - applications run in unmanaged memory environment
  - no support for user- and kernel-space memory regions
  - no management at process context switches
  - platform-specific memory area using regions
    (start address, size, attributes)
  - memory pool

Interfaces and Drivers
  - IDB (interface descriptor block): splits into
    - hardware descriptor: physical channel
    - software descriptor: end point where packet should be routed
  - HW descriptor can have additional SW descriptor to suport subinterfaces


Kernel Support Services
  Subsystems
    - allow image to be built modularily
    - some are optional
    - declared by subsystem header
    - main components
      - entry point: called to initialize subsystem
      - class specification: when it should be called during platform init
      - dependencies

  Registries and Services
    - function vector table, calling sequence
    - service: instance of associated fuction vectors, processes or values
               with particular invocation characteristic
    - registry: collection of associated services
